```xml
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    package="com.madhub.instagramfollowerbot">

    <!-- 
    Problem: Android applications often require specific permissions to function correctly.
    Solution: The following permissions enable the necessary features for managing social media accounts.
    -->

    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />
    <!-- 
    This permission solves the problem of needing internet access to communicate with social media APIs,
    allowing for the retrieval and management of user account information.
    -->

    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE" />
    <!-- 
    Addresses the challenge of understanding the network state to perform operations effectively,
    ensuring that actions are taken only when a network connection is available.
    -->

    <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />
    <!-- 
    This permission overcomes the limitation of saving user-generated content and logs,
    enabling the application to store information locally on the device for easy access and management.
    -->

    <application
        android:allowBackup="true"
        android:icon="@mipmap/ic_launcher"
        android:label="@string/app_name"
        android:roundIcon="@mipmap/ic_launcher_round"
        android:supportsRtl="true"
        android:theme="@style/Theme.AppCompat.Light.NoActionBar">

        <!-- 
        Problem: The main entry point of the application needs to be defined for users to interact with the UI.
        Solution: Registering the MainActivity class as the launcher activity presents the user with the 
        necessary interface to begin social media management operations.
        -->
        <activity
            android:name=".MainActivity"
            android:exported="true">
            <intent-filter>
                <action android:name="android.intent.action.MAIN" />
                <category android:name="android.intent.category.LAUNCHER" />
            </intent-filter>
        </activity>

        <!-- 
        Problem: Continuous operation is crucial for effective social media management.
        Solution: The AutomationService will handle background tasks for scheduling and performing actions 
        on the user's social media accounts without requiring constant user interaction.
        -->
        <service
            android:name=".AutomationService"
            android:enabled="true"
            android:exported="false">
            <!-- 
            This service is designed to run automated tasks in the background, ensuring that social media 
            operations can be performed 24/7, leveraging MadHub's capability of working on real devices 
            or cloud-based solutions.
            -->
        </service>

    </application>

</manifest>
```

### Explanation of the Code:
1. **Permissions**:
   - Internet access is crucial for communication with social media platforms.
   - Network state access helps in optimizing operations based on connectivity.
   - Write external storage permission allows saving user data for ongoing management tasks.

2. **Component Registration**:
   - **MainActivity** serves as the starting point for users, providing an interactive interface for operations.
   - **AutomationService** ensures that tasks run continuously in the background, maximizing efficiency and adhering to best practices in social media management.

